## 1. Project Overview

### 1.1 Purpose

NLMongo is a full-stack web application that enables users to interact with MongoDB databases using plain English sentences instead of MongoDB Query Language (MQL). It bridges the gap between non-technical users — business analysts, managers, product owners — and the raw power of a document database.

### 1.2 Problem Being Solved

Traditional database querying requires:
- Knowledge of MongoDB syntax and operators (`$gt`, `$match`, `$group`, etc.)
- Understanding of collection schemas and data types
- Familiarity with aggregation pipelines for complex analysis

This creates a bottleneck where non-technical stakeholders must depend on engineers or data analysts to retrieve information. NLMongo eliminates this bottleneck.

### 1.3 Core Capabilities

| Capability | Description |
|---|---|
| Plain English Querying | Users type questions in natural language |
| Automatic Query Translation | AI converts questions to valid MongoDB queries |
| Query Transparency | Generated query is shown to the user |
| Schema Exploration | Users can browse collections and fields |
| Result Presentation | Data is shown in structured, paginated tables |
| Query History | Previous queries are saved for the session |

### 1.4 Scope & Constraints

**In Scope:**
- Read operations: `find`, `aggregate`, `countDocuments`
- Single-database connections
- Web-based interface (desktop-first)

**Out of Scope (v1.0):**
- Write operations (insert, update, delete)
- Multi-database connections
- Role-based access control
- Mobile application

