## 10. Security

### 10.1 Operation Whitelist

Only the following MongoDB operations are allowed to execute:

- `find`
- `aggregate`
- `countDocuments`

Any AI-generated query requesting `insert`, `update`, `delete`, `drop`, or other write/admin operations is rejected with a `403` error before reaching MongoDB.

### 10.2 Rate Limiting

API calls are rate-limited to prevent abuse and control AI API costs:

```javascript
// Default: 30 requests per minute per IP
const limiter = rateLimit({
  windowMs: process.env.RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS || 60000,
  max: process.env.RATE_LIMIT_MAX_REQUESTS || 30,
  message: { error: "Too many requests. Please wait before trying again." }
});
```

### 10.3 CORS Policy

Only origins defined in `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` can communicate with the API.

```javascript
app.use(cors({
  origin: process.env.ALLOWED_ORIGINS?.split(",") || ["http://localhost:5173"]
}));
```

### 10.4 HTTP Security Headers (Helmet)

Helmet is used to set the following headers automatically:

- `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`
- `X-Frame-Options: DENY`
- `Strict-Transport-Security`
- `Content-Security-Policy`

### 10.5 API Key Protection

- AI API keys are stored only in server-side `.env` files.
- The frontend never receives or stores any API key.
- All AI API calls are made server-side.

### 10.6 Input Sanitization

User input is passed to the AI API as a plain string. It is never directly interpolated into any MongoDB query. The AI generates the query; the query then goes through validation before execution.

